
1Ô∏è‚É£ FAQ: When to Set State in React?

üëâ State should be set:

When component data changes dynamically

When UI needs to re-render based on data

On component mount or user interaction

‚ùå Do NOT set state directly while creating the component unless required.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Component Mount Phase (useEffect)
How to configure mount & unmount?

React uses useEffect hook.

Syntax:
useEffect(() => {
  // code runs on mount

  return () => {
    // cleanup on unmount
  };
}, []);

Key Points:

Empty dependency array [] ‚Üí runs only once

Component mounts on first render

To re-run effect ‚Üí add dependencies

3Ô∏è‚É£ JavaScript Data Types in React

React uses all JavaScript data types.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Number Type

JavaScript supports:

Integer

Float

Decimal

Exponential

Binary

Octal

Hexadecimal

BigInt

Examples:
10, -10, 3.14, 23.33, 2e3, 0b1010, 0o456, 0xABC

Number Formatting Methods:

toFixed()

toPrecision()

toLocaleString()

Example:
const price = 45000;
price.toLocaleString("en-IN", { style: "currency", currency: "INR" });

5Ô∏è‚É£ Parsing Numbers
parseInt("10");
parseFloat("10.5");
isNaN("abc"); // true

6Ô∏è‚É£ Boolean Type
Boolean Values:

true

false

Important Notes:

JSX does NOT allow statements (if/else)

Use expressions only

Boolean can be treated as:

0 ‚Üí false

1 ‚Üí true

Example:
const [status] = useState(true);

<p>{status === true ? "True" : "False"}</p>

7Ô∏è‚É£ String Type

React supports all JS string formats:

Single Quotes ' '

Double Quotes " "

Backticks `` `

Backticks (Template Literals)

‚úî Allow JS expression binding

const name = "React";
`Welcome ${name}`;

Binding Difference:

${} ‚Üí JavaScript binding

{} ‚Üí React JSX binding

8Ô∏è‚É£ Dynamic Class Binding
const [styleClass] = useState("bg-danger text-white");

<p className={`border p-2 ${styleClass}`}>Hello</p>

9Ô∏è‚É£ String Methods (Same as JS)
Common Methods:

length

charAt()

charCodeAt()

indexOf()

lastIndexOf()

slice()

split()

trim()

startsWith()

endsWith()

includes()

match()

toUpperCase()

toLowerCase()

üîü null & undefined
Properties:

Same meaning as JavaScript

Defined using keywords null and undefined

Example:
const [name, setName] = useState();

setName(prompt("Enter Name"));

<p>{name === null ? "Name required" : name}</p>

1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ Symbol Type

New primitive data type

Used to create unique object keys

Helps in hiding object properties

1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ Object Type in React
Key Points:

Object stores data + logic

JS object with data = JSON

Object is key-value pair collection

Example:
const [product] = useState({
  id: 1,
  name: "TV",
  price: 45000
});

<p>{product.name}</p>

Object Operations:

Read keys ‚Üí Object.keys(obj)

Check key ‚Üí "key" in obj

Delete key ‚Üí delete obj.key

Hide key ‚Üí Symbol

1Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ Array of Objects
Definition:

Array is a collection

Can store object elements

Example:
const [data] = useState([
  { id: 1, name: "A" },
  { id: 2, name: "B" }
]);

1Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ Array Type in React
Declaration:

[]

new Array()

Array Methods:

forEach()

map()

toString()

slice()

find()

filter()

1Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£| Feature       | map() | forEach() |
| ------------- | ----- | --------- |
| Returns data  | ‚úÖ Yes | ‚ùå No      |
| Used in JSX   | ‚úÖ Yes | ‚ùå No      |
| Creates array | ‚úÖ     | ‚ùå         |

1Ô∏è‚É£6Ô∏è‚É£ Presentation in React

Presentation is totally dependent on the requirement

‚úÖ Summary

‚úî React uses JS data types
‚úî JSX supports expressions only
‚úî useEffect handles lifecycle
‚úî map() is mandatory for rendering lists
‚úî State drives UI
